data.name: lblOptimization.Text
data.value:
Please note that the following function works only on an Intel SSD.
Optimizes Intel SSDs using Trim functionality. Intel recommends running the Intel SSD Optimizer once a week.
Other features will be disabled while the optimization is running.

data.name: lblDiagnostic.Text
data.value:
Please note that the following function works only on an Intel SSD.
Full Diagnostic Test: Tests the read and write functionality of an Intel SSD. Read Scan checks every Logical Block Address (LBA) for a hard error. Data Integrity uses the free capacity of the SSD to write random data and then verify the data. - Approximate run time is an hour or more depending on available free space.
Quick Diagnostic Test: Tests the basic functionality of an Intel SSD using a small sample area of free space. This test does not affect existing data. - Approximate run time is 3 minutes. 5 GB of free space is required to run this test.
Other features will be disabled while the diagnostic scan is running.

data.name: lblFirmware.Text
data.value:
Please note that the following function works only on an Intel SSD.
Updates the selected Intel SSD to the latest firmware available with this version of the Intel MAS. Minimize system use during this operation. After a successful update, reboot the system to complete the update process.
Other features will be disabled while the update process is running.
